# XDS / Exchange prototypes — mandatory rules

**Canonical repo:** https://github.com/ashwinirappa-wq/xds-prototypes  
Static HTML in sibling projects should load tokens from that repo’s `public/design-system/` (see Rule 1).

## Figma sources (reference first)
- **XDS Exchange Design System:** https://www.figma.com/design/S5vzHnfEkTU1uETKnVOl7x/XDS---Exchange-Design-System
- **Exchange Brand Playbook:** https://www.figma.com/slides/Oyb9M17fbUWZl4C7ZTO3jQ/Exchange-Brand-Playbook

## Rule 1 — Import the shared CSS kit
For HTML under `unified-campaign/`, use paths relative to the `Cursor` root:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="../_shared/xds-prototypes/public/design-system/tokens.css">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="../_shared/xds-prototypes/public/design-system/components.css">
```

If the HTML file lives elsewhere, adjust the relative path so it resolves to `xds-prototypes/public/design-system/*.css`.

## Rule 2 — Use design tokens for all visual properties
Never hardcode colours, spacing, font sizes, border radii, or shadows. Always use `var(--xds-*)` tokens.

## Rule 3 — Dark theme by default
Page root should use `var(--xds-surface-page)` and `var(--xds-text-primary)`.

## Rule 4 — Use `.xds-*` component classes
Use design-system component classes for buttons, cards, inputs, badges, tables, tabs, nav, info blocks, modals before writing custom CSS.

## Rule 5–10
Same typography, spacing, colour semantics, badges, navigation, and “check Figma before inventing styles” as before — tokens and classes are defined in `tokens.css` / `components.css` inside **xds-prototypes**.
